commText: Abhishek Sharma and Head are at the crease. Abhishek Sharma is on strike. Starc will open the attack
Starc to Abhishek Sharma, no run, fuller length delivery and shaping away from wide of off, Abhishek saw the width and went hard on the drive, beaten by the awayswinging delivery

Starc to Abhishek Sharma, no run, a nervy poke, short of a good length and slanting across the left-hander - Abhishek plays away from his body, hangs his bat out to dry and is beaten on the outside edge

Starc to Abhishek Sharma, no run, short and wide of off, would've been called as a wide had Abhishek let it go, he went chasing after that and toe-ended it to cover, was in the air, but bounced short of the fielder

Starc to Abhishek Sharma, 2 runs, a run-out chance? A better throw would've had Abhishek well short - might've been struggling had Gurbaz thrown down the stumps, he was well away and misses his shy - on a good length and well wide of off, Abhishek leans across, plays with an open face and then guides it backward of square on the off-side - his call for the second, was always a risky one and he was struggling, but Ramandeep's throw is well wide of the stumps
Starc to Abhishek Sharma, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Starc to Abhishek Sharma, out Bowled!! Peach, an absolute peach and Abhishek has no answers - this is some start from Starc once again, big game player and he's come to the fore once again. Outlandish stuff from the Aussie legend, angled in, drew Abhishek forward and then nipped away wickedly, opened up the left-hander like a can of beans and clips the outside of his off-stump. Don't think Abhishek could've done anything about it, he just puts his head down and walks away. Abhishek Sharma b Starc 2(5)
STAT: Shreyas Iyer becomes the first captain to lead two different franchises in IPL grand finals - Delhi Capitals in 2020 and Kolkata Knight Riders in 2024.
Rahul Tripathi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Tripathi, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, dropped in front of cover-point for a quick single
Vaibhav Arora, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, no run, edged, but the ball drops well in front of the keeper - was the cutter from Vaibhav, stopped onto Tripathi as he shaped for the back-foot poke, hit very high on the bat and lands in front of the keeper
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, no run, nice channels from Vaibhav - short of a good length and just outside off, Tripathi is very fidgety as he pushes forward, gets a soft edge that rolls through to slip
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, no run, this is a good start from KKR - Vaibhav bowls into the surface and follows Tripathi as he backed away, hit high on the bat and lobbed wide of the bowler

Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, leg byes, 2 runs, on a good length and angling into the pads, past Tripathi's flick and rolls off the pads towards square leg - Gurbaz with the chase, but he can't prevent the batters from coming back for the second
A break in play, will allow SRH to relax and get grip on the situation. Gurbaz is getting his pads changed and hence the break in play
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, 1 run, short of a good length and angling into the right-hander, nudged behind square on the on-side for a single
Vaibhav Arora to Head, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Vaibhav Arora to Head, out Caught by Gurbaz!! Edged and caught! SRH have lost both openers now, this is some start from Vaibhav - on a good length and seaming across the left-hander, Head's feet hardly went anywhere, stayed leg-side and ended up feeling for the ball, a thin edge and Gurbaz does the rest, moving across to his left. Shocker of a start and SRH's fans are already looking downcast. Head c Gurbaz b Vaibhav Arora 0(1)
Aiden Markram, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Tripathi, FOUR, nicely played, too straight from Starc, on the pads and it's flicked away nonchalantly, races away to the long leg boundary
Starc to Tripathi, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the pads, clipped behind square on the on-side for a single
Starc to Markram, no run, on a good length and at the stumps, Markram gets right behind the line and defends it to the on-side
Highest partnership scoring rate for a pair in an IPL season (500+ runs) 13.46 Head - Abhishek in 2024 12.46 Narine - Salt in 2024 11.49 Du Plessis - Maxwell in 2023 10.55 Kohli - De Villiers in 2016

Starc to Markram, FOUR, edged and four, fuller length delivery and pushed across the right-hander, Markram saw the width and went hard on the drive, gets a thick edge that races away past the lone slip
Highest SR in Powerplay in an IPL season (100+ runs) 250.94 Jake Fraser McGurk (2024) 209.29 Travis Head (2024) 208.33 Ajinkya Rahane (2023) 202.95 Abhishek Sharma (2024) 198.59 Sunil Narine (2018)

Starc to Markram, no run, the big inswinger and Markram nearly played all around it, full and shaping back into the right-hander, Markram was looking to flick, closed the face of the bat and squeezes an under-edge onto the pad
Starc to Markram, no run, fuller length delivery at the stumps, driven straight to the fielder at mid-on
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, wide, on a length and sliding down leg, Tripathi shuffled a long way across on the lap and missed, called as a wide
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, wide, Vaibhav slips one full and down leg, was the attempted cutter which went wrong, called as a wide
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, 1 run, tad fuller and just outside off, dropped in front of cover-point and he's off for a quick single
Vaibhav Arora to Markram, no run, on a good length and nipping back into the right-hander, Markram gets right behind the line and punches it to mid-off
Travis Head last four innings 0(1) vs PBKS 0(2) vs KKR 34(28) vs RR 0(1) vs KKR
Vaibhav Arora to Markram, 1 run, fraction fuller and angling into the right-hander, tucked to the left of mid-wicket for a single
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, no run, Vaibhav drags the length back and shortens the length - Tripathi charged down the track, has a slash and is beaten on the inside edge
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, wide, Vaibhav loses his line and pushes one down the leg-side, called as a wide
Vaibhav Arora to Tripathi, 1 run, tight line from Vaibhav - short of a good length and angling into the right-hander, dropped in front of point for a quick single
Vaibhav Arora to Markram, no run, short of a good length and shaping back into the right-hander, Markram has no room to free his arms and pushes it back at the bowler
Starc to Tripathi, no run, Starc pushes this one wide of off and gets it to shape away further, a loose waft as Tripathi flays at that and misses
Starc to Tripathi, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Starc to Tripathi, out Caught by Ramandeep Singh !! A massive leading edge, high into the night sky - Ramandeep calls for the catch, goes reverse cup and held on with ease. SRH in disarray at the moment - wrong choice of shot from Tripathi, was looking to counter Starc, but this was a low percentage shot, on a length and angling across the right-hander - Tripathi was shaping for the whip, but he's played against the angle, closed the face of the bat and the edge went straight up. Tripathi c Ramandeep Singh b Starc 9(13) [4s-1]
Nitish Reddy, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Starc to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, back of a length and angling across the right-hander, Nitish makes use of Starc's pace and runs it down to third man
Starc to Markram, 1 run, on a good length and well wide of off, a punchy drive past cover for a single
Starc to Nitish Reddy, no run, fuller length delivery and well wide of off, Nitish shapes for the drive and is beaten on the outside edge
Starc to Nitish Reddy, no run, on a good length and angling across the right-hander, left alone

Highlights (1-5 overs) - Starc strikes in the first over and knocks over Abhishek - Vaibhav sends Head packing for a golden duck - Couple of fours in Starc's 2nd over to get SRH going - Vaibhav bowls 3 wides in his 2nd over but still goes for just 6 runs - Tripathi runs out of patience and becomes Starc's second wicket
Vaibhav Arora to Markram, wide, loose from Vaibhav, drags the length back, but it's miles wide of off, called by the umpire
Vaibhav Arora to Markram, FOUR, slapped, that'll relieve some pressure off Markram - width on offer, he gets on top of the bounce and then clatters the cut over cover, bounces away to the ropes

Vaibhav Arora to Markram, FOUR, cracking shot, Vaibhav doesn't learn, bowls one short and wide of off - Markram rides the bounce and then hammers the cut over cover-point, did it hit the cushions on the full? No, it's on the half-volley and it's a four, but back-to-back boundaries for Markram

Vaibhav Arora to Markram, 1 run, a direct hit and Markram might've been struggling, despite the big dive - punched it sweetly towards mid-off and set-off for a quick single, the ball bounced nicely into Shreyas's hands, he shies and misses - a direct hit would've sent Markram packing
Vaibhav Arora to Nitish Reddy, no run, the slower bouncer from Vaibhav, Nitish watches it closely, drops his hands and lets it go, on the bounce to the keeper

Vaibhav Arora to Nitish Reddy, SIX, nicely played, banged in short and down leg, Nitish swivels across, picks the length and then pulls it into the stands at long leg, must give him plenty of confidence
Vaibhav Arora to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, fuller length delivery on off, driven to the left of mid-off for a quick single, 17 off the over
Harshit Rana, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshit Rana to Nitish Reddy, FOUR, crunched, a friendly start from Harshit - short and wide of off, Nitish rides the bounce and cracks it square past point for a boundary
Harshit Rana to Nitish Reddy, 1 run, on a length and just outside off, dabbed down towards third man for a single
Harshit Rana to Markram, wide, too short and too wide from Harshit, Markram threw his hands on the cut and missed, called as a wide
Harshit Rana to Markram, no run, the slower cutter, grips the surface and angles back into the right-hander - Markram is cramped for room and is beaten on the inside edge
Harshit Rana to Markram, 1 run, another slower ball from Harshit - width on offer and Markram went hard on the cut, mistiming it to the off-side for a single
Harshit Rana to Nitish Reddy, no run, on a good length and just outside off - Nitish stays on the back-foot and finds cover with the drive, was the slower ball once again
Harshit Rana to Nitish Reddy, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Harshit Rana to Nitish Reddy, out Caught by Gurbaz!! Edged and caught! Change of pace has completely undone Nitish here - after three slower ones, Harshit bowls the perfect awayswinger, pitched on off and nips away slightly - Nitish's feet went nowhere, he's waiting on the back-foot for the slower ball to arrive, shapes for the drive and nicks off to the keeper. Second catch of the night for Gurbaz and KKR are firmly on top at the moment. Nitish Reddy c Gurbaz b Harshit Rana 13(10) [4s-1 6s-1]

They've taken the strategic break. Assume it'll be Klaasen walking in next, SRH desperately need their two big overseas buys to get them out of trouble. This ain't a 200-run pitch, if there's no dew, anything more then 160 would be definitely competitive
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Heinrich Klaasen, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Markram, no run, dropped short and wide of off, Markram backs away and cuts it to backward point
Narine to Markram, 1 run, flighted delivery outside off, Markram stays back and punches it uppishly, to the left of cover for a single
Mitchell Starc World Cup 2023 Group stage: 10 wkts in 8 matches Knockouts: 6 wkts in 2 matches IPL 2024 Group stage: 12 wkts in 12 matches Playoffs: 5* wkts in 2 matches
Lowest Powerplay scores for SRH in IPL 2024 37/2 vs RR Hyderabad 40/3 vs PBKS Mullanpur 40/3 vs KKR Chennai * 45/4 vs KKR Ahmedabad
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, nudged down to long-on for a single
Narine to Markram, no run, flighted delivery on middle, stops onto Markram and forces the miscue, lobbed in the air and dropped wide of the fielder at mid-wicket - a lucky break for Markram
Narine to Markram, 1 run, flighted delivery on off, punched square on the off-side for a single
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, fraction short and wide of off, cut away to deep cover for a single

Harshit Rana to Klaasen, FOUR, edged and four, on a good length and just outside off, satys slightly low, so did Klaasen as he pushed forward, gets the edge and runs away through the vacant slip region
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, 1 run, the slower cutter now, pushed into the gap wide of point for a single
Harshit Rana to Markram, 1 run, slower short ball outside off, cut away square on the off-side for a single
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, no run, another slower ball from Harshit, Klaasen pushes it to cover
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, no run, another slower off-cutter, Klaasen hangs back and pushes it back at the bowler
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, 1 run, back of a length and well wide of off, steered away to deep cover for a single
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, tossed up on off, Klaasen closes the bat-face and works it to long-on
Narine to Markram, 1 run, dropped short by Narine - Markram backs away and punches it to deep cover for a single
Narine to Klaasen, 1 run, tossed up on off, punched off the back-foot to long-on
Narine to Markram, no run, the off-break, grips and turns off the pitch - Markram went back on the flick and missed, clipped the back thigh and dropped beside the stumps
Narine to Markram, no run, tossed up on off, defended back at the bowler
Narine to Markram, no run, flighted delivery on off, Markram can't beat backward point with the cut
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Highlights (6-10 overs) - Vaibhav is smashed for 17 runs as SRH end the powerplay well - Harshit strikes in his first over, Nitish nicks off - Narine starts with a tidy over - Harshit's slower balls are gripping the surface - Another quiet over by Narine
Russell to Klaasen, 1 run, back of a length delivery, Klaasen short-arm jabs it through mid-wicket
Russell to Markram, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Markram, out Caught by Starc!! Russell has done this all season. He has come on and struck almost immediately. This is a massive wicket as SRH's title hopes relied on this pair and he has split them apart. Short of length delivery and bit of extra bounce, Markram goes for the pull but because of the bounce he gets it high on the bat, straight to long-on and Starc makes no mistake. There is some spongy bounce on this wicket and Russell bowled the perfect length for that. Markram c Starc b Russell 20(23) [4s-3]
Shahbaz Ahmed, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Shahbaz Ahmed, 2 runs, leg-lined delivery, Shahbaz tucks it square on the leg-side and races back for the second
Russell to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, bouncer angled across, Shahbaz sways out of the line and allows it to pass
Russell to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, slanted outside off, Shahbaz had the width and he throws his bat, beaten on the outside edge

Russell to Shahbaz Ahmed, SIX, streaky! But Shahbaz and SRH won't be complaining. They need a bit of luck to go their way. Well-directed short ball and Shahbaz goes for the pull instinctively, gets a big top-edge and the ball flies over Gurbaz, just clears the rope
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, no run, flatter and fraction short, Klaasen cuts and picks out cover
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, 1 run, googly on the shorter side, Klaasen punches it wide of long-off and settles with a single
Round the wicket to Shahbaz
Chakaravarthy to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, drifts in with the angle, Shahbaz prods forward and defends
Chakaravarthy to Shahbaz Ahmed, no run, wrong 'un and Shahbaz picks it off the surface, stabs it to backward point
Chakaravarthy to Shahbaz Ahmed, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Chakaravarthy to Shahbaz Ahmed, out Caught by Narine!! Another bowler that strikes in his first over - Starc, Vaibhav, Harshit, Russell and now Varun. Full marks for captain Shreyas Iyer for his bowling changes. The sweep is a dangerous shot to play on a pitch that has some bounce, Shahbaz makes that mistake and pays the price. He tries his best to roll his wrist over and keep it down, but the ball balloons to short fine, Narine runs back and takes it as calmly. Shahbaz Ahmed c Narine b Chakaravarthy 8(7) [6s-1]
61/4 is the lowest total for SRH at the halfway mark of the innings this season.
SRH have once again been forced to use their impact sub - Abdul Samad comes in for Travis Head. The Aussie's IPL final is done..
Abdul Samad, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Chakaravarthy to Abdul Samad, 1 run, googly that is bowled flatter, Samad stays back and knocks it to sweeper cover
Russell to Abdul Samad, 2 runs, I0$ full delivery at the stumps, Samad flicks in front of square and picks up a brace
Russell to Abdul Samad, 1 run, I0$ good length ball around off, Samad eases it to long-on
Russell to Klaasen, 1 run, I0$ good length ball and Klaasen is rooted to the crease, brings his bat down and bunts it to long-on
Russell to Abdul Samad, wide, slips the slower ball down leg, Samad allows it to pass and collects the wide
Russell to Abdul Samad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Abdul Samad, out Caught by Gurbaz!! Second wicket for Russell. Excellent catch by Gurbaz. KKR on fire. Russell even does a little jig. The impact sub makes no impact and SRH slip further. Fullish delivery outside off, this ball did not move but Samad played it well away from the body, he reached for it and had a push, the ball flies off the outside edge and Gurbaz dives to his right to take the catch. Abdul Samad c Gurbaz b Russell 4(4)
Pat Cummins, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Russell to Cummins, FOUR, short and outside off, Cummins plays the cut late and hence places it behind square on the off-side. The ball teased the third man fielder before beating him to the fence
Russell to Cummins, 1 run, I0$ slower ball around off, Cummins pats it into the off-side and retains strike

Chakaravarthy to Cummins, FOUR, cheeky! Very unlike Cummins but he's come out with intent at least. He shapes to play the paddle but the line is outside off and he adjusts to reverse lap it fine of short third
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, byes, 1 run, shuffles a long way across to play the scoop, the ball spins past leg-stump and even Gurbaz does not glove it cleanly
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, no run, quicker and drifts in, Klaasen is rooted to the crease and ekes out an inside edge onto the pad

Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, 2 runs, brilliant work by Ramandeep. Short of length delivery, Klaasen makes room and punches it in front of square, Ramandeep runs across from sweeper and dives to make the stop - one-handed pick up and throw
Chakaravarthy to Klaasen, 1 run, flatter and quicker, Klaasen punches it firmly to long-off
Lowest score at the fall of 7th wkt in an IPL final 57/7 CSK vs MI Kolkata 2013 77/7 SRH vs KKR Chennai 2024 * 79/7 MI vs RPS Hyderabad 2017 92/7 RCB vs CSK Chennai 2011
Chakaravarthy to Cummins, no run, carrom ball and Cummins does not pick it, he looks to steer but the ball breaks away to beat the outside edge
Harshit Rana [2.0-0-14-1] is back into the attack
Harshit Rana to Klaasen, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Harshit Rana to Klaasen, out Bowled!! Dragged on! This is a massive moment in the game. Klaasen was the last recognised batter for SRH and he too is walking back to the dugout. Harshit is off on a celebratory run. Slower ball outside off, Klaasen reaches for the drive but the ball grips a tad, takes the inside edge and crashes into the stumps. KKR are two wickets away from bowling out SRH. Klaasen b Harshit Rana 16(17) [4s-1]
Jaydev Unadkat, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Harshit Rana to Unadkat, no run, fullish delivery around off, Unadkat pushes it back to Harshit

Kolkata review! Shreyas was not interested. But Harshit and Ramandeep from mid-wicket have forced him to send it upstairs. This is a poor one. The impact itself is outside leg-stump. Missing the stumps by a long way. Not Out

Harshit Rana to Unadkat, no run, KKR lose a review. Harshit's adrenaline took over there and he got support from Ramandeep. Gurbaz said not to go upstairs but Shreyas went with his bowler's word. Good length ball angled in, Unadkat is beaten on the inside edge and struck on the back pad, the impact was outside leg and the ball was missing leg-stump comfortably
Harshit Rana to Unadkat, no run, banged in short and gets it to climb sharply, Unadkat has a slash and is beaten on the top-edge
Harshit Rana to Unadkat, no run, fuller now and drawing Unadkat into the drive, he still can't put bat on ball, beaten on the outside edge
Harshit Rana to Unadkat, no run, wicket maiden! Short ball outside off, Unadkat looks to pull and is nowhere close to connecting

Over Summary (11-15 ov) * Markram holes out to long-on off Russell, OUT for 20 * Shahbaz gets going with a streaky maximum * Varun strikes in his first over, Shahbaz OUT for 8 * Another failure for Samad, edges behind for 4 * Cummins gets going with a boundary past point * Harshit delivers the killer blow, Klaasen OUT for 16 * Unadkat survives a LBW review on 0
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack

Narine to Cummins, byes, FOUR, some bonus runs for SRH. The off-break and it spins a mile, Cummins attempts the reverse sweep and misses it by a long way, Gurbaz does not move down leg to glove it and the ball runs away
Narine to Cummins, 1 run, spinning into the pads, Cummins works it backward of square leg
Slip added
Narine to Unadkat, no run, off-break and Unadkat does not pick, he prods forward and is beaten on the inside edge, struck on the pad

Narine to Unadkat, 1 run, carrom ball and Unadkat shapes to play the scoop, gets it off the glove and Shreyas was left wrong-footed, he was moving to his left from slip expecting the ball to go there, but it lobs wide of silly point and drops safely

Narine to Cummins, 1 run, dropped! Starc puts down a sitter. He's just given his Aussie mate a life. This was bowled slower and hence Cummins decided to go down town, gets more height than distance and Starc comes around from long-on, goes with both hands but is not able to hang on. That was a simple chance and Starc made a mess of it
Narine to Unadkat, 1 run, in the air and safe.. Unadkat goes for the reverse sweep and gets it off the top-edge, the ball balloons towards short third man and lands just in front of the fielder

Timeout! SRH are in tatters and their goal from here would be to bat out 20 overs. If they can do that and get somewhere around 120-130 then there's at least something for the bowlers to work with. But KKR are looking like they will get the two wickets before that.
Harshit Rana to Unadkat, 1 run, I0$ slower ball outside off, Unadkat eases it wide of cover
Harshit Rana to Cummins, no run, another off-pace delivery and Cummins checks his push to cover
Harshit Rana to Cummins, no run, I0$ off-cutter and it grips the surface, Cummins once again checks his shot and angles it to point
Harshit Rana to Cummins, 2 runs, I0$ short and banged into the surface, Cummins slaps it in front of square and Russell tidies up from sweeper cover. SRH bring up their 100

Harshit Rana to Cummins, SIX, fine effort from Russell but he can't prevent the six. Pace on full delivery, the line is outside off and Cummins had the room to free his hands, lofts it to deep extra cover and Russell sprints across from sweeper, gets there with a slide and hangs on, but the momentum takes him over the rope and he can't let go of the ball earlier. Much needed hit for SRH
Harshit Rana to Cummins, 1 run, slower ball outside off, Cummins allows it to arrive and guides it to third man
Narine to Cummins, 1 run, slower off-break and Cummins nudges it to mid-wicket, Rinku keeps it to a single
Narine to Unadkat, 1 run, carrom ball around off, Unadkat goes for the reverse sweep and gloves it fine, Harshit with a diving stop
Narine to Cummins, 2 runs, fraction short and at the stumps, Cummins shuffles and pulls it behind square on the leg-side, couple more
Narine to Cummins, 1 run, short of length carrom ball, Cummins opens the bat face and angles it to point

Kolkata review! What happened there? The ball hit the stumps and light them up but the bails don't fall. So KKR have decided to review for LBW as the ball touched something before going on to hit the stumps. No bat as per UltraEdge. Ball-tracking shows it to be hitting leg-stump. OUT
Narine to Unadkat, THATS OUT!! Lbw!!

Narine to Unadkat, out Lbw!! KKR get the wicket. This was an off-break that turns in sharply, Unadkat leans forward to push it down the ground, gets beaten on the inside edge and struck on the pad, the ball then goes on to hit the off-stump but the bail does not dislodge. Shreyas decides to review for LBW and ball-tracking shows it to be smashing into leg-stump. One way or the other KKR have the wicket. Unadkat lbw b Narine 4(11)
Bhuvneshwar Kumar, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Bhuvneshwar, no run, short of length delivery, Bhuvneshwar knocks it to a vacant point region and Cummins denies the single
Andre Russell [2.0-0-19-2] is back into the attack
Russell to Cummins, no run, slower ball on the stumps, Cummins swings across the line and misses. He was early into the shot..
Most wickets in middle overs (7-15) in IPL 2024 17 Varun Chakravarthy (KKR) 13 Sunil Narine (KKR) 12 Andre Russell (KKR) 12 Yuzvendra Chahal (RR) 12 Kuldeep Yadav (DC)
Russell to Cummins, no run, I0$ off-pace delivery and Cummins toe-ends the pull to deep mid-wicket. He denies the single
Russell to Cummins, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Russell to Cummins, out Caught by Starc!! SRH are bowled out for 113. Starc makes amends for his earlier drop. Russell ends with a 3-fer. This was full and pace on, in the slot and hence Cummins was able to get under it, he connects cleanly but does not get the elevation, strikes it flat and straight to long-on, Starc barely had to move to take the catch. Cummins c Starc b Russell 24(19) [4s-2 6s-1]

21:13 Local Time, 15:43 GMT: What just happened? It will take a while to wrap our heads around this SRH innings. Yes, the surface was difficult and not a belter but surely it was not a 113 kind of pitch. There was swing, bounce and grip - KKR made the most of that by bowling in the right areas and never allowing SRH to get going. Starc once again struck in the first over and this time it was Abhishek who could got an absolute peach. Head managed to avoid Starc but succumbed to Vaibhav in the very next over. SRH's top order woes in the last few games came to the fore again as Tripathi too departed inside the powerplay. KKR didn't relent as they kept picking wickets at regular intervals, Markram and Klaasen got starts but could not convert them. Cummins played a cameo towards the end and got the total past 100. This is looking more like KKR's final to lose at the moment unless SRH come up with a magical bowling performance. Back soon with the chase..
Lowest totals in IPL finals 113 SRH vs KKR Chennai 2024 * 125/9 CSK vs MI Kolkata 2013 128/6 RPS vs MI Hyderabad 2017 129/8 MI vs RPS Hyderabad 2017
Lowest totals for SRH (IPL) 96 vs MI Hyderabad 2019 113 vs MI Hyderabad 2015 113 vs KKR Chennai 2024 * 114 vs PBKS Dubai 2020

Starc 2/14 Arora 1/24 Harshit 2/24 Narine 1/16 Russell 3/19 Varun 1/9 Only the second time six different bowlers have taken a wicket in an IPL final; the first being MI vs CSK at Eden Gardens in 2013.
This is the first instance of no player from a team reaching 30 in an IPL final across 33 innings (the highest being Pat Cummins' 24).

Andre Russell: Very happy, very happy, especially getting three wickets in this game. We all know how important this game is. As big players, we all stood up tonight. Very happy with how I am bowling and very happy with how everyone's bowling. Just being disciplined, bowling to the plans and trying to bowl less bad balls. My fitness is a big part of that but mentally I am in a better space. I was mentally down for the last few years, going through a lot.
